  "prompt": "Is there any existing source code for Android video filtering like the snapchat?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several open-source and sample projects available for Android video filtering similar to Snapchat-like effects:\n\n1. Open Source Libraries:\n- GPUImage for Android\n  - GitHub: https://github.com/CyberAgent/android-gpuimage\n  - Provides real-time camera and video filters\n  - Supports various image processing effects\n\n- Camera Filters by Google\n  - GitHub: https://github.com/googlearchive/camerafilters\n  - Sample project demonstrating camera filter implementation\n\n2. Advanced Video Filtering Frameworks:\n- OpenCV for Android\n  - Comprehensive computer vision library\n  - Supports advanced image and video processing\n  - Website: https://opencv.org/android/\n\n- ML Kit by Google\n  - Provides face detection and image processing\n  - Can be used for creating AR-like effects\n\n3. Sample Implementations:\n- Android Camera2 Filter Sample\n  - GitHub repositories demonstrating filter techniques\n  - Often include basic image processing examples\n\n4. Commercial SDKs:\n- Banuba Video SDK\n- Twilio Programmable Video\n- Agora.io Video SDK\n\nRecommended approach:\n1. Start with GPUImage\n2. Explore OpenCV\n3. Consider ML Kit for advanced effects\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific implementation technique?",
